This game is fit for anyone. It's difficult, but not frustrating. It's colorful, but not kiddie. It's simple, but not easy. The game revolves around one mechanic, stretching and latching to other objects. That sounds silly (badum tssss), but it is executed very well. The thing about it is, the first few levels let you figure out the controls, and then they start throwing obstacles in there. This is when the game gets a little more complitcated. You can't stat stretched forever as some obstacles move , and stretchingeaves you vulnerable. This simple mechanic turns this game into a fun and creative plaatformer-puzzle game hybrid. The game is fit for anyone to play. Completionists and hardcore gamers can set out to collect every gem and they will feel some challenge at some parts of the game. Casual gamers and children playing will be pushed along at a steady pace, one that makes the game feel relaxed rather frustrating. Instead of yelling and getting angry when dying, you'll instead just say "Woops, now I know what I did wrong." The art and music styles are beautiful, they remind me of something you'd see on the Game Boy Advance. Colorful, clear, pixelated graphics that fit the game very well. I would recommend this game to anyone that likes games at all. It is a very good game.
